<HEADLINE>
FT  08 APR 94 / UK Company News: United Friendly depressed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A sharp increase in underwriting losses last year depressed profits at
United Friendly, the life and general insurance company.
At the pre-tax level they fell by Pounds 3m to Pounds 20.4m. The final
dividend, however, is increased to 11p making a 16.5p (14.5p) total, payable
from earnings of 21.2p (23p) per share.
A poor performance by the motor insurance division was largely responsible
for the profits decline. Against the industry trend, underwriting losses on
motor widened to Pounds 8.4m.
</TEXT>
