FT  08 APR 94 / UK Company News: Development Securities buys portfolio of
London properties
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Development Securities, the revamped Clayform Properties headed by Mr Martin
Landau, the property entrepreneur, has acquired a Pounds 92m portfolio of
primarily office properties.
The company, which will assume Pounds 64m of debt with the portfolio, is
raising Pounds 19.3m through a placement to partly fund the Pounds 29m net
purchase price.
Since Mr Landau joined the board of Development Securities last June, the
company has issued Pounds 80m of new shares and built up net assets of
Pounds 83m following this latest transaction.
Mr Robert Ware, joint managing director, said: 'We're now at a size where we
can grow organically.' He pointed out that the company would not issue more
equity for at least a year.
The latest purchase comprises 17 properties, mainly in the Greater London
area. They currently produce net rental income of Pounds 7.3m, representing
a yield of 7.9 per cent.
Development Securities will pay Pounds 1m in cash and issue 10m shares at
30p. The remaining Pounds 22m will be paid via a loan note or cash. It paid
Pounds 3m for an initial option on the properties, which were purchased from
private companies controlled by Mr RJ Livingstone.
The company will raise Pounds 18.3m net of expenses from the placement of
64.66m new shares, priced at 30p. There is a clawback for existing
shareholders on a 3-for-10 basis.
