<TEXT>
Thailand's largest cement and building materials conglomerate, Siam Cement,
has tentatively agreed to build a steel plant in a joint venture with Nippon
Steel and Mitsui &amp; Co of Japan, writes William Barnes in Bangkok.
The Dollars 580m (Pounds 395m) plant would supply up to 1m tonnes of
