FT  07 APR 94 / International Company News: Foodland in red but holds payout
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Foodland Associated, the Australian grocery group, is holding its interim
dividend at 12 cents a share in spite of extraordinary charges which sent it
into the red for the seven months to January.
Net earnings rose marginally to ADollars 18.8m (USDollars 13.4m) from
ADollars 18.1m, including a ADollars 7.5m abnormal loss. But a ADollars
32.2m extraordinary loss sent the company ADollars 12.4m into the red for
the period.
