FT  07 APR 94 / UK Company News: Telegraph pays directors Pounds 2.72m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Directors of The Telegraph newspaper group received total emoluments of
Pounds 2.72m in 1993, up from Pounds 1.51m the previous year.
A large part of the increase represented a one-off Pounds 480,000 payment to
Mr Daniel Colson for his work in connection with the group's investment in
John Fairfax Holdings, the Australian newspaper group, where he is chief
executive.
