148,000 to Pounds 237,000. In addition, The Telegraph pays two thirds of the
cost of Mr Black's office at Hollinger, The Telegraph's parent, and pays
Hollinger for other services, such as advice on acquisitions. These costs
totalled Pounds 1.04m (Pounds 813,000).
During 1993, The Telegraph and Hollinger combined to take a 18.7 per cent
stake in Southam, the Canadian newspaper publisher.
